# GitHub Pages static site

This repository is a **static site** published to **GitHub Pages** via **GitHub Actions** (`.github/workflows/pages.yml`). Treat it as client-only HTML/CSS/JS.

## Layout and build

- **Source** lives under [`docs/`](docs/): multi-page HTML, [`docs/css/main.css`](docs/css/main.css) (Tailwind entry), [`docs/js/site.js`](docs/js/site.js) (imports CSS for Vite).
- **Vite** [`vite.config.mjs`](vite.config.mjs): `root` is `docs/`; **`pnpm run build`** writes the deployable site to repo-root **`dist/`**.
- **GitHub Pages base path** is **`/diensten-bij-mij/`** (project site). It must stay in sync with Vite `base` in [`vite.config.mjs`](vite.config.mjs).
- **Local dev**: `pnpm dev` — open the app under the configured `base` (e.g. `/diensten-bij-mij/`). **`pnpm preview`** serves **`dist/`** after a build.

## Stack and markup

- **Tailwind CSS v4** (utilities + `@theme` tokens in `main.css`), **`@tailwindcss/typography`** for prose blocks, **`dark:`** tied to **`prefers-color-scheme`** via `@custom-variant` in CSS.
- Follow [`tailwind.mdc`](tailwind.mdc) for tokens, ordering, and accessibility.
- Prefer **semantic HTML** (`main`, `nav`, `header`, `article`, `section`, proper heading order, labels on controls).

## Hard constraints

- **No server-side code**, server frameworks, or API routes in this repo. No reliance on Node at runtime in the browser beyond what the static build emits.
- Client-side `fetch` to **public** third-party or static JSON endpoints is fine; do not introduce a backend owned by this project unless the user explicitly changes that assumption.

## Examples

```html
<!-- Vite injects hashed CSS/JS from the module script -->
<script type="module" src="/js/site.js"></script>
```

```text
❌ Serving only raw `docs/` on Pages without running `pnpm build` (Tailwind would not compile)
✅ Action uploads `dist/` after `pnpm build` — Pages source = GitHub Actions
```
